%N A395363 Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) = number of inequivalent n X k matrices of +-1's, for 1 <= k <= n.
%C A395363 The equivalence is the same as for Hadamard matrices: permutations of rows, permutations of columns, multiplication of rows by -1, multiplication of columns by -1.
%H A395363 Albert L. Wells Jr, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/0095-8956(84)90025-X">Even signings, signed switching classes, and (- 1, 1)-matrices</a>, Journal of Combinatorial Theory, Series B 36.2 (1984): 194-212.
